100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On January 28, 1926, British explorer Sir Ernest Shackleton was laid to rest in South Georgia, following his death in January 1922, marking the end of an era in Antarctic exploration. In the realm of politics, the League of Nations continued its efforts to resolve disputes between member nations, with ongoing discussions regarding the situation in the Ruhr Valley. Meanwhile, the United States faced ongoing debates over Prohibition, with calls for reform gaining traction amid rising public discontent.
